Controversial Dutch filmmaker shot dead on Amsterdam street by Stephanie van den Berg ADDS filmmaker's quotes AMSTERDAM, Nov 2 AFP Dutch filmmaker Theo van Gogh, who had received threats over a controversial film he made about Islam, was shot and stabbed to death Tuesday while cycling on an Amsterdam street, officials said.
Dutch politicians and commentators were united Tuesday in their condemnation of the murder, in broad daylight on an Amsterdam street, of controversial filmmaker Theo van Gogh and called for calm together with representatives of the Dutch Muslim community.
